					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A commentary on the Zohar, Numbers.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Aramaic of the Zohar</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546">
							<locus from="1r" to="156v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Or yaḳar (Be-midbar)</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">אור יקר (במדבר)</title>
							<note>
								<p>The colophon on folio 145v has been crossed out. The colophon at the end (folio 277v) combines the author's colophon with the entry of the scribe, copied from another manuscript. </p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/12317536">Cordovero, Moses ben Jacob, 1522-1570</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/12317536">קורדוברו, משה, 1522-1570</persName>
							</author>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">היום ילדתיהו אני הצעי' משה בן לא"א הר' יעקב קורדואירו בחדש אדר ראשון משנת השכ"ג ליציר' פה צפת תות"ב, ונשלם ההעתק' ר"ח ניסן <date calendar="Hebrew">השמ"ז</date>.<locus n="277v"/>
							</colophon>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">תם ונשלם ת"ל ע"י הצעיר <name type="person" role="scribe">שלמה בכמ' שמואל מרושינה</name> זצל לכבוד והדר המשכיל דורש אלקי' כמה' <name type="person" role="scribe">יעקב פוייט'</name> יצ"ו פה <name type="place">אסטי</name> י"ח כסלו <date calendar="Hebrew">שמ"ב</date>.<locus n="145v"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the second half of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>156 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>270</height>
										<width>205</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>185/230</height>
										<width>155/180</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>156 folios (+3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 4 at the end). Folio 1 is a paper flyleaf.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Original Hebrew foliation, 1-134 (agreeing with folios 12-145).</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="5 33" writtenLines="5 33">
									<p>Uniform layout. Text and commentary mostly written in parallel columns.</p>
									<p>Visible hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Initial words in larger square characters.</p>
									<p>Running titles.</p>
									<p>A number of marginal notes and comments.</p>
									<p>Folios 6, 8-11 blank.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Italian cursive scripts (for the main text and for the commentary) of the second half of the 16th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Ya῾aḳov ben Mordekhai Pogeṭṭi</name>: inscribed in the colophon, folio 145v. <name type="person" role="scribe">Shelomoh ben Shemu᾿el</name>: inscribed in the colophone, folio 145v.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="1r" to="146r"/>: the commentary on these folios probably written by Shelomoh ben Shemu᾿el. The rest of the manuscript written by Ya῾aḳov ben Mordekhai Pogeṭṭi.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Boniforte del Asinary</name>: Italian censor (active 1575-1599 in Asti): inscribed with his name: 'Visto et coretto per me Boniforte del Asinary' (folio 145v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">V</ref>.</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Hieronimus Carolus</name>: inscribed with his name: 'Inqu. Asti. Die 19 Febr. 1582' (folio 145v).</p>
						</additions>
